==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conglutination
<hw>Con*glu`ti*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conglutinatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>conglutination</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A gluing together; a joining by means of some tenacious substance;
junction; union.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Conglutination</qex> of parts separated by a wound.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conglutinative</ent>⟦br⟧
